runs.comm: short of a length, accurate, slight shape back in, defended to mid-off
CK walks down, Pathan stays short of a length, pushed to square leg. That's 8 balls for no runs for CK in this tournament
stays short of a length, no room, defended again - nine balls, zero runs for CK this tournament. Add to that a missed stumping
he is finally off the mark, and hoe desperately. Gets width here, but drives it just to the right of straight extra cover. CK is gone for all money, dives desperately, but Yuvraj misses the stumps
this one swings down the leg side, and is called a wide
short of a length, no room, hit to cover
timber. Slogs at thin air. Pathan pitches it up, swings it just enough, and Hales has swung at it in an ungainly manner. No contact made, and the middle stump is flattened out
bowled from wide of the crease, then gets it to leave him against the angle. Left alone
full, on off, driven back to him
short of a length, angling in, nearly dragged on like in the first game, but he is safe this time
long half-volley on the pads, and CK has taken full toll. Straight and over mid-on, lovely timing, good follow through, and the high elbow for the cameras. India hit their first six in the 20th over
short of a length, wide, CK moves forward and across, and drives it on the up, between cover and cover-point
short of a length, angling in, pushed to midwicket
short of a length, moving back in, gets an inside edge onto his pad
nice delivery, swinging in, short of driving length, pushed back to him
Wright is continuing from where he left it the other night. This one is floated wide, doesn't swing back, and Wright shimmies down to loft it over mid-off. Lovely connection

That doesn't look right. Just doesn't. Short ball, no swing, hits him high on the thigh, and he is given. Possibly pitched outside leg, possible edge onto it, possibly going over the stumps. That had too many doubts with it. It's a brave decision all right, and it is right too. Pitched just inside the line, stayed low, no edge, hitting the top of leg
Morgan charges first ball, and is beaten by the swing. Nowhere near that one
short of a lenght, accurate, stays low, Morgan gets the bat down just in time
short, wide, punched away, straight to cover-point
short and wide again, cut away, but the third man is really square, and keeps them down to one
bouncer, sharp, 132ks, in his face, gets Morgan to top-edge it, but it doesn't carry to the deep man on the leg side
that's smacked away. Lashed away. No respect shown to the quick. Just plonks the front foot down, and drives this short-of-a-length delivery for a flat six over extra cover
more crash-bang-wallop. Short of a length again, this time CK opens the front leg and slogs this between mid-on and midwicket
sharp bouncer, 136ks, outside off, and CK pulls out of the shot
length ball, angling in, beats the inside edge, but it is headed down leg
short of a length, outside off, late-cut straight to short third man
swinging down the leg side, flicks the pad on the way, they don't go for the leg-bye
short of a length, well down leg, and with the keeper, all he needs is a tickle. Dhoni gets a glove to it, but it would be really harsh to call it a drop
short of a length, outside off, coming back in, pushed to cover
nicely played. The third man is up, he gets the width, opens the face late, and places it between Dhoni and short third man
Morgan leaves the crease first ball, is beaten in the flight, kicks it away

We've been expecting you, Mr Singh. And is he fired up? Bowls the quick arm ball, Morgan goes back to cut. Poor choice. Like patting a burning cat. That has squeezed under his bat to knock the middle stump out. Harbhajan is pumped

and an appeal for a stumping. The doosra here, slow in the air, dipping at him, Bairstow is tentative in defence, the ball beats the outside edge, Dhoni breaks the wicket, but JB has not left the crease for even a moment
short of a length, flat, quick, pushed to midwicket
offbreak now, turning into the pads, defended to leg
beaten on the sweep, but he has got himself outside the line. Yet another wicket-maiden. This tournament has had a few
worked into the on side for one
premeditated sweep, gets a single to long leg
full, on off, driven to long-off for one
low full toss, hit nicely, but straight to extra cover
short, wide, but it skids through to beat the cut

poor batting. Doesn't read the googly, goes for the big slow sweep, leaves him a gate big enough for a train to squeeze through, and is bowled. Fair to stay Jonny is not quite as comfortable against spin as he is against pace
short of a length, outside off, nicely late-cut past slip for two
short of a length, outside off, pushed for one to cover
short of a length again, run past slip by Buttler this time, gets two again
flighted, slow through the air, defended back
doosra, and he hasn't read it at all. Tentative push again, and lucky not to edge it
reverse-sweep. That counters Harbhajan for the moment. Flighted outside off, and he gets it past the wide slip. Middled

Oh England. They are coming apart against spin again. Chawla tosses up, gets a legbreak to turn for a change, Kieswetter drives on the up. He is nowhere close to the ball, and has allowed it enough time to turn away and take a thick edge. Sharp catch by Kohli at slip
flighted on off, pushed back to him
tossed up legbreak, thrown up wide too, Bresnan drives, and is beaten
it's the googly, Chawla is loving it. Huge appeal for lbw as Bresnan hasn't read it. But this is headed down leg
short of a length, angling down, Bresnan fails to make contact
flighted legbreak, Bresnan is tentative as he pushes, and is beaten comprehensively. Another wicket-maiden
short of a length, on off, goes deep into the crease, works it around the corner for one
straighter one, Bresnan plays the forward-defensive
quicker one, Bresnan pushes this wide of Harbhajan for one
looks to reverse this, plays it straight to slip, on the bounce
Kohli has nearly pulled off a blinder here. Quick delivery, Buttler looks to punch it, Kohli anticipates and moves wide with the shot, but the edge is too sharp for him to hold on to

England are falling apart faster than a cookie under Steve Waugh's book. Bresnan might well have read the Hindi scrip better than he has read spin tonight. Finally brings out the sweep, and limply top-edges it to deep square
a low full toss, and he dinks it fine with a paddle sweep
full, outside off, pushed wide of point
another poor shot. Tweets before the ball that he is going to play the paddle. Chawls has seen the tweet, and bowls it full and wide. Toe-ends it up in the air, but it is safe
full again, pushed to cover-point
pre-meditated reverse this time, gets a bottom edge that bounces into the pitch, and over slip
short of a length, driven to sweeper-cover for one

not sure I have seen worse batting against spin ever. They are making up their mind what shot to play even before the bowler is starting to run towards the stumps. Buttler backs away early, Harbhajan stays on a length and just outside off, and then breaks through under the bat, which is playing a nothing shot
sharp offbreak, Swann keeps it out
length ball, turning in, pushed to midwicket

oh what is happening here? A procession. They are batting as if wearing those glasses you get at 3d movies. No attempt to read spin, although you can't blame Swann when the top order has failed miserably. Dances down the wicket, walks past a doosra, and is stumped by a mile
short of a length, on off, defended back
length ball, on off, turns in slightly, defended
Respite? What respite? Dinda bowls short, Broad pulls, and finds deep midwicket to perfection. He could have picked that fielder out had it been a nail in haystack
backs away and pulls, goes wide of deep midwicket, gets a four
backs away and pulls again, gets a single to mid-on
backs away and hits a short ball over extra cover. He just swung and hoped for the best, but gets the runs. They have now gone past the lowest total of all time
that's effective. Follows him with the short ball, and he gets some glove to lob it over the keeper
shot. Makes room, gets a length ball, chips it over point
pushed to long-on for one
flighted legbreak, beaten on the sweep. Somebody tell England, there is playing field in front of square too
short of a length, punched away to deep cover
full and straight, Dhoni collects it on a half-volley, goes for the stumping, but the third umpire tells Simon T that Dernbach dragged the back foot back in time
slider, worked away into the leg side for one
flighted outside off, driven to long-off
low full toss, driven to long-on for one
flighted outside off, driven along and down the ground for one
slow, slow offbreak, beaten comprehensively
it's all over. No third umpire required. Finn comes down the track, gets an inside edge and charges off. Short fine leg fires in the throw to catch Dernbach short
